{"name":"Force Staff","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p><span dir=\"ltr\" style=\"left: 95.0416px; top: 742.782px; font-size: 12px; font-family: sans-serif; transform: scaleX(0.734273);\">Weapon is Two-Handed</span></p>\n<p>Force weapons have no special abilities unless a psyker wields them. In the hands of anyone else, a force weapon is simply another sword or staff, though still extraordinarily rare and valuable beyond compare. When a psyker channels his mental energies through the psychoreactive circuitry and arcane runes covering the weapon, however, it becomes tremendously powerful. His will and rage multiplied into a force that can rend armour and reality alike, a psyker with such a weapon is a warrior to be rightly feared.</p>","availability":"extremely-rare","weight":2,"class":"melee","type":"","range":0,"rateOfFire":{"single":0,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10","damageType":"impact","penetration":"2","clip":{"max":0,"value":0},"reload":"","special":"Force","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Meele/skull-staff.svg","effects":[],"_id":"FPodQJ2wCchzqjkD"}
{"name":"Nemesis Daemon Hammer","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>No single weapon encapsulates the Ordo Malleus quite like the nemesis hammer. Each handcrafted weapon is unique in some way, displaying fine artistry and destructive brutality in equal share. Consecrated and warded in a complex series of rituals that take years to complete, it is anathema to the daemonic; a single blow is often enough to send a Daemon screaming back into the Warp. A nemesis hammer is a one-handed weapon, but when used with two hands it gains the Concussive (X) quality, where X equals the user&rsquo;s psy rating.</p>","availability":"near-unique","weight":10,"class":"melee","type":"","range":0,"rateOfFire":{"single":0,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"2d10+1+2*SB","damageType":"energy","penetration":"8","clip":{"max":0,"value":0},"reload":"","special":"Nemesis Daemon HammerDaemonbane, Force, Power Field, Unwieldy, DMG+2*SB","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Meele/warhammer.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ICYd9lXGCxhYdX5g"}
{"name":"Sanctus Hammer","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>A common item for those of the Ordo Malleus possessing psychic powers, these weapons allow an Inquisitor or Acolyte to smite Daemons with the purest of energies. A force hammer requires two hands to use, unless the wielder has a Strength bonus of 5 or higher.</p>\n<p>Sanctus</p>\n<p>Inquisitor Augustine commissioned Sanctus to amplify her and her followers&rsquo; considerable martial skills. Crafted from unusually lightweight materials, each long-handled hammer still packs the same punch as its heavier cousins. Beyond its use in melee, each Sanctus hammer holds a secret within: a small chamber loaded with purified promethium that gives the hammer a hidden burst of explosive might. A Sanctus hammer is a two-handed weapon. It also includes an exterminator cartridge (see page 163 of the Dark Heresy Core Rulebook) loaded with Incinerator ammunition (see page 40).</p>","availability":"near-unique","weight":6,"class":"melee","type":"","range":0,"rateOfFire":{"single":0,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"2d10+6","damageType":"energy","penetration":"4","clip":{"max":0,"value":0},"reload":"","special":"Balanced, Concussive (4), Daemonbane, Force, Power Field, DMG+2*SB","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Meele/warhammer.svg","effects":[],"_id":"aRmLTsx9iXkmXWT2"}
{"name":"Animus Hammer","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>A common item for those of the Ordo Malleus possessing psychic powers, these weapons allow an Inquisitor or Acolyte to smite Daemons with the purest of energies. A force hammer requires two hands to use, unless the wielder has a Strength bonus of 5 or higher.</p>\n<p>Animus</p>\n<p>Small of stature, Inquisitor Rufinius acted as the conclave&rsquo;s only psyker. Cursed with a wide range of psychic abilities, his commissioned hammer incorporated a crystalline matrix that helped to calm and centre his power. A potent force weapon in its own right, Animus is the most powerful type of Illyricum hammer. An Animus hammer acts as a psy-focus (see page 177 of the Dark Heresy Core Rulebook). If the wielder possesses the Psyker trait, the weapon adds +1 to his psy rating.&nbsp;</p>","availability":"near-unique","weight":8,"class":"melee","type":"","range":0,"rateOfFire":{"single":0,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"2d10+10","damageType":"energy","penetration":"4","clip":{"max":0,"value":0},"reload":"","special":"Daemonbane, Force, Power Field, Unwieldy, DMG+2*SB","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Meele/warhammer.svg","effects":[],"_id":"cA6LIHgsEryJCCGs"}
{"name":"Force Sword","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Force weapons have no special abilities unless a psyker wields them. In the hands of anyone else, a force weapon is simply another sword or staff, though still extraordinarily rare and valuable beyond compare. When a psyker channels his mental energies through the psychoreactive circuitry and arcane runes covering the weapon, however, it becomes tremendously powerful. His will and rage multiplied into a force that can rend armour and reality alike, a psyker with such a weapon is a warrior to be rightly feared.</p>","availability":"near-unique","weight":5,"class":"melee","type":"","range":0,"rateOfFire":{"single":0,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+1","damageType":"rending","penetration":"2","clip":{"max":0,"value":0},"reload":"","special":"Balanced, Force","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Meele/piercing-sword.svg","effects":[],"_id":"nqFdhiAKb1rPJ6Q8"}
{"name":"Force Hammer","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>A common item for those of the Ordo Malleus possessing psychic powers, these weapons allow an Inquisitor or Acolyte to smite Daemons with the purest of energies. A force hammer requires two hands to use, unless the wielder has a Strength bonus of 5 or higher.</p>","availability":"extremely-rare","weight":10,"class":"melee","type":"","range":0,"rateOfFire":{"single":0,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"2d10","damageType":"rending","penetration":"0","clip":{"max":0,"value":0},"reload":"","special":"Force, Unbalanced","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Meele/warhammer.svg","effects":[],"_id":"oiS63VyaXfGPc7Xu"}
{"name":"Tempus Hammer","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>A common item for those of the Ordo Malleus possessing psychic powers, these weapons allow an Inquisitor or Acolyte to smite Daemons with the purest of energies. A force hammer requires two hands to use, unless the wielder has a Strength bonus of 5 or higher.</p>\n<p>Tempus</p>\n<p>Completed years after its owner&rsquo;s death under a cloud of suspicions concerning its desired purpose, Tempus contains a rare stasis device that generates pulsing waves of anti-chronal energy. The Core Thetan Magi that created the pattern consider it so dangerous that there is a large bounty for the return of any working example, yet so few exist and there have been no sightings in decades. Some within the conclave fear that the Tempus weapons have followed the first Illyricum hammer into the hands of the Ruinous Powers. Once per game session, as a Full Action, a character wielding Tempus may smite the ground, causing a blast with a radius of 2d10 metres. Each other character in this area must make a Hard (&ndash;20) Agility test or lose a Half Action during his next turn; if a character fails with two or more degrees of failure, he loses his Full Action instead. This is a two-handed weapon.</p>","availability":"near-unique","weight":14,"class":"melee","type":"","range":0,"rateOfFire":{"single":0,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"2d10+4","damageType":"energy","penetration":"6","clip":{"max":0,"value":0},"reload":"","special":"Daemonbane, Force, Power Field, Unwieldy, DMG+2*SB","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Meele/warhammer.svg","effects":[],"_id":"vkcjKtG3ceH11ctd"}
